        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: directly deliver completed media fallback",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Keep generated media tasks active until completion delivery is confirmed, so duplicate/retry checks see the task while delivery is still pending.\n- Add duplicate and recent-completion guards for image, video, and music generation requests.\n- Add a direct generated-media fallback when requester-agent/message-tool delivery misses the completed media, while preserving the active wake/message-tool handoff path from `upstream/main`.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test src/agents/subagent-announce-delivery.test.ts src/agents/tools/media-generate-background-shared.test.ts src/agents/tools/image-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/music-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/video-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/video-generate-background.test.ts src/agents/image-generation-task-status.test.ts src/agents/video-generation-task-status.test.ts src/agents/tools/music-generate-tool.status.test.ts src/agents/tools/video-generate-tool.status.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.session-lock.test.ts`\n- `pnpm changed:lanes --json --base upstream/main`\n- `pnpm check:changed --base upstream/main`\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n- `git merge-tree HEAD upstream/main`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Generated media completions no longer finish their task before visible delivery is confirmed, and generated media gets a direct channel fallback if the requester-agent/message-tool handoff misses the media.\n\nReal environment tested: Local source checkout on macOS, rebased on current `upstream/main` (`79197b3196`).\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran the focused media/session Vitest command listed above, the base-pinned changed lane/check commands listed above, and a merge-tree check against `upstream/main`.\n\nEvidence after fix: Focused Vitest passed with 11 test files and 181 tests. `pnpm check:changed --base upstream/main` passed core/coreTests lanes. `git merge-tree HEAD upstream/main` exits cleanly with no conflict output beyond the synthetic merge tree id.\n\nObserved result after fix: Active requester media completions attempt the upstream wake/gateway handoff first, then use direct generated-media fallback only if handoff misses the media. Pending announce-agent runs are not raced by the direct fallback.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live Discord/Telegram media delivery and CI, which had not run yet at PR creation time.\n",
